metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, Futatsuiwa from Sado is significantly more complex than the typical song, having above average scores in Chord Complexity, Melodic Complexity, Chord-Melody Tension, Chord Progression Novelty and Chord-Bass Melody.
key_conclusion: Futatsuiwa from Sado has sections analyzed in the following keys: D♯ Minor, E Minor, A Minor,  and F♯ Minor.  Click on the linked cheat sheets for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: most, if not all chords here are broken power chords and don't include the third
replaced major/mixolydian ii with dorian ii so that chord does not become supermodal in the relative major
flute harmony in third/fourth lines intermingle, so this is an attempt to try and take the most prominent note as the lead
